Basic Outbound Authentication:

To create new basic auth credentials remove the authMode and add the below payload.


	{
		"templateKey": "authMode",
		"values": [
			"NEW"
		]
	},
	{
		"templateKey": "httpAuthCredentials",
		"parameters": [
			{
				"templateKey": "userName",
				"values": [
					"Administrator"
				]
			},
			{
				"templateKey": "password",
				"values": [
					"manage"
				]
			}
		]
	}

OAuth2 Outbound Authentication:

We can also provide custom oauth2 token by replacing the "authMode" to "NEW" and provide the "oauth2Token" like below


	{
		"templateKey": "authMode",
		"values": [
			"NEW"
		]
	},
	{
		"templateKey": "oauth2Token",
		"values": [
			"oauth2_token_value_here"
		]
	}

NTLM Outbound Authentication:

To pass the custom credentials change the auth mode to "NEW" and add the below entries.

{
	"templateKey": "httpAuthCredentials",
	"parameters": [
		{
			"templateKey": "userName",
			"values": [
				"Administrator"
			]
		},
		{
			"templateKey": "password",
			"values": [
				"manage"
			]
		}
	]
}

to make it transparent change the authMode to "TRANSPARENT".

Kerberos Outbound Authentication:

To provide custom kerberos credentials change the authMode to "NEW" and add the below entries.

{
	"templateKey": "kerberosCredentials",
	"parameters": [
		{
			"templateKey": "clientPrincipal",
			"values": [
				"value"
			]
		},
		{
			"templateKey": "clientPassword",
			"values": [
				"value"
			]
		},
		{
			"templateKey": "servicePrincipal",
			"values": [
				"value"
			]
		},
		{
			"templateKey": "servicePrincipalNameForm",
			"values": [
				"hostbased" // or username
			]
		}
	]
}

Content Based Routing:

The supported payload identifiers are xpath,jsonpath and regex.

XPath Payload Identifier:
{
	"templateKey": "payloadIdentifier",
	"parameters": [
		{
			"templateKey": "expressionType",
			"values": [
				"xpath"
			]
		},
		{
			"templateKey": "expression",
			"values": [
				"/request/header/enableSSL"
			]
		}
	]
}

Regex Payload Identifier:
{
	"templateKey": "payloadIdentifier",
	"parameters": [
		{
			"templateKey": "expressionType",
			"values": [
				"xpath"
			]
		},
		{
			"templateKey": "expression",
			"values": [
				"/request/header/enableSSL"
			]
		}
	]
}

Also we can add multiple rules for content based routing by adding the section with template key "contentRules".

Dynamic routing with Header:

Change the routingConditionKey to "header" and add "routingConditionValue" like below.

{
		"templateKey": "routingConditionKey",
		"values": [
			"header"
		]
	},
	{
		"templateKey": "routingConditionValue",
		"values": [
			"dynamicRoutingHeader"
		]
	}

Load Balancing Routing:

To add multiple endpoints in the load balancing routing, add another entry for template key "lbRouteTo" object with the needed details like below.

{
	"templateKey": "lbRouteTo",
	"parameters":[....]
},
{
	"templateKey": "lbRouteTo",
	"parameters":[....]
}

